title: tony stark is tired
body:
tony stark is tired of the world

tony stark is tired every morning when he wakes up

and tony stark is tired every night when he goes to sleep

he tries to explain to pepper, he tries holding her close and whispering that he is tired, that he is so endlessly tired that sometimes it feels like he’ll fall asleep and never wake up,

and tony always bites his tongue and keeps himself from whispering the words he knows would hurt her more than anything, the words that hurt him to keep to himself

the fact that tony stark is angry every morning he wakes up, that tony stark is tired of living

he is tired of losing the people he loves and he is tired of the guilt and shame and worry

he is tired of being hurt over and over and over again by the people he trusts

and tony stark is tired of being jaded and cynical

tony stark wants to a live a life where he isn’t tired, where he’s happy

where he has a partner by his side and a baby in his arms

tony stark wakes up tired and somedays all he wants is to stay in bed and hold pepper as close as he can, but as always

he has to get up, he has to keep on living, because tony stark is tired, but if he doesn’t get up, he’s scared he never will, so tony stark wakes up and he helps people and he finds different reasons to get out of bed

but each night, tony stark’s muscles ache and his heart hurts and he is happy but he is tired because he is sick of carrying phones of the people he loves in his pockets,

just waiting for a call he fears might never come

and tony stark is tired, because every day feels like a warning for something worse

and tony stark is tired, because he doesn’t know who to trust anymore

and he doesn’t know what’s real anymore

and all he has is pepper and rhodey and every morning he wakes up tired and he wakes up scared and he wakes up angry

and tony stark is tired because his arms hurt and his mind is exhausted and his heart is broken

tony stark is tired because every morning feels like en eternity and the night no longer helps him

tony stark is tired because each nightmare feels like reality and each day feels like a dream

tony stark is tired because nothing feels real anymore and he’s happy but he’s tired 

tired of living, tired of breathing, tired of waking up

tony stark is happy

but tony stark is so endlessly tired that he doesn’t know what his legs would feel like without the 100 pound weights that drag them down.

tags: thor loki doctor strange x reader
body:
Thor’s Daughter

“If you’re still doing requests do you think you could do a Dr Strange fluff? Where maybe they have a crush on a team mates daughter? (Like maybe Thor’s Daughter)”

@cat-of-ninetails

Word Count: 1321

Warnings: None

It didn’t take Tony Stark or another other geniuses to realize that Doctor Strange had taken a liking to Y/N. Almost everyone knew it. As if the way that he lost focus or stopped mid-sentence when you entered a room wasn’t enough to tell, he even stuttered over his words and his voice got deeper and more “macho”. The nights that you stay over at the Tower, he tends to walk around in sleeveless muscle shirts and tighter fitting sweats. Tony noticed right away, finding it a little gross but also hilarious.

“Hey guys!” You exclaim, treading into the room with a bag over your shoulder and a suitcase in your other hand. Stephen jumps, startled by your voice. He jolts around, his eyes landing on you. “Y/N. Didn’t know you were coming!” Steve exclaims, striding over to you and giving you a friendly hug. Stephen watches Steve’s hands closely, uncomfortable with his hands on you. Yeah, Cap is old-fashioned and a gentleman, but he’s still a man. “Dad didn’t tell you?” You respond as he pulls away, his gentle hands falling back to his sides before he takes notice of your bags and goes to pick them up for you. This makes Stephen a little more pissed, believing that Steve is trying to win you over.

“Hello, Y/N.” He greets as he strides over to you, his hard eyes landing on Steve for a moment as he begins walking toward one of the guest rooms. You wrap your arms around Stephen’s larger form, smiling against his chest contently as his large rough hands find your back, holding you close. You subtly inhale the intoxicating smell of whatever cologne he is wearing, making him all the more appealing. You are sure that no one other than Steve knows about your serious crush on Doctor Strange himself, so you pull away before the hug can be considered too long. “How are you, Stephen?” You ask him.

Little do you know how weak you make him in the knees at hearing his name on your tongue. “I am well. How have you been, Y/N?” He responds. Little does he know that your name on his lips has the same effect on you. “I’ve been alright.” You say, your eyes leaving his as you notice Natasha approaching you. Something about the look in your eyes makes Stephen not believe you, feeling like there is something bothering you. Before he can think anything of it, your father comes booming into the room, as per usual. “Strange! Good to see you!” Thor exclaims, giving his friend a hefty pat on the shoulder as he heads past him toward the fridge. “Lady Natasha! Has Tony bought what Y/N requested?” Thor questions Widow, whom takes a casual seat on one of Tony’s luxurious sofas. “Yes Thor. Top shelf.” She responds. Stephen raises his brow curiously at Y/N, who chuckles lightly, approaching her father. “Daddy, I told you not to bother them. It was mostly a joke.” Stephen bites his lip, almost not hearing anything you said after “daddy”. He doesn’t have a daddy kink, but something about the way you said it, although totally innocent, makes him want you to say it to him. For you to submit yourself to him, want to please him, to be his innocent little girl.

Unfortunately for him, being that you are Thor’s twenty-three year old daughter, you are off-limits to each and every member of the team. Thor wants Steve and Tony to protect you from men attempting to make advances on you, as a matter of fact. “Uncle Loki!” You exclaim, causing every head in the room to turn towards the door. Loki stands there, a slightly stunned look on his face. You run over to him, clearly very excited to see him, which confuses Stephen very much. He knows that the god of mischief is your uncle, but he didn’t think you were very close to him. “Hello, dove.” He greets, opening his arms to you as you leap into them dramatically. It had been a while since you saw him, after he disappeared for a while after faking his death. Stephen wishes that you would leap into his arms like that, causing him to look away as you clung onto your uncle, overjoyed to see him.

Later in the day, you had decided to take a nap, due to the long plane-ride from India where you were doing some overseas charity work, building homes and helping those in need. You apparently insisted that Thor not teleport you, because you enjoyed the human experiences, even jet-lag. Stephen watched longingly as you trudged into the room sleepily, in more comfortable clothes than earlier, which consisted of sleeping shorts and a t-shirt, your hair in a messy bun. You swear that you look like a mess, but Stephen is captivated. So much so, that he forgets not to stare, and Loki catches him watching you.

He clears his throat, bringing Stephen back to reality, his head shooting to the mischievous man. “See something you like?” He asks, his face anything but playful. He has that same look that Thor had when he overheard Tony making a flirty comment toward you when he first met you. Not quite as “ready to kill” but still very dangerous. “What? No?” He responds, awkwardly attempting to play off the fact that he was just literally entranced by your presence alone. You are paying no attention to them, too busy searching for the cereal that Thor asked Tony to get for you.

Loki continues staring at Stephen, trying to figure out what to do. He could lash out at him, could tell Thor or you, or he could do the responsible thing. He’s supposed to be trying to turn a new leaf, and he knows that you care for Stephen, therefore harming him would be harming you. “Right. Do tell why you are staring at my niece then.” He presses, unfamiliar with this protective feeling he has over you. “Who is staring at your niece?” Booms throughout the room. Stephen’s eyes shoot up at Thor’s very large, aggravated body towering over him from the sofa. You obviously hear Thor and started approaching the three men in the sitting room. “What’s going on?” You ask, wondering why your uncle and father are gathered around Stephen. “Do you have feelings for my daughter?!” Thor booms, his muscles tensing, very irritated that one of his colleagues is seriously interested in his precious not-so-little girl.

“Hold on hold on hold on. You guys are jumping the gun.” Stephen defends himself, until his eyes fall on you. They immediately soften, a look that both Loki and Thor are very much familiar with. As opposed to normal, this enrages Thor more, whereas it softens Loki. “Brother… He is looking at her the way you look at Jane.” Loki reasons, bewildering Stephen. He turns away from you, embarrassed that his secret is out. “Dad. Stop it. I’m an adult.” You demand, stepping between Stephen and Thor. He glares at the man behind you, then finally sighs and relaxes a little. “Do not hurt her.” He threatens, then retreats off to another room, probably to sulk about how you’re growing up, even though you already did quite a few years ago. Loki looks between the two of you, before slowing heading out of the room as well. “So is it true?” You ask once the two of you are alone. Stephen doesn’t meet your eye at first, unsure if he should try to play it off or not. He isn’t even sure what he wants at this point.

“I hope so, cuz I have feelings for you, Stephen.” You mutter, ducking your eyes, not catching his stunned face as you walk out of the room, leaving him standing there frozen in place, attempting to process what just happened.
